title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 9, subtit. A, ch. I, pt. 2 - Executive Orders (Malcolm A. Wilson)
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 9, subtit. A, ch. I, pt. 2 - Executive Orders (Malcolm A. Wilson)

State Regulations
§ 2.1 - Executive Order No. 1: Relating to the continued validity of executive orders previously issued
§ 2.2 - Executive order no. 2: amending and superseding the executive orders of may 23, 1967 [section 1.23, supra], april 16, 1968 [section 1.25, supra], october 8, 1969 [section 1.34, supra], october 8, 1970 [section 1.40, supra], and april 2, 1971 [section 1.47, supra], designating the health planning commission as the state's official long-range health planning agency
§ 2.3 - Executive Order No. 3: Relating to extended unemployment insurance benefits

§ 2.7 - Executive Order No. 7: Relating to extended unemployment insurance benefits
§ 2.8 - Executive Order No. 8: Amending and superseding Executive Order No. 39 [Section 1.39], dated June 10, 1970, consenting to the transfer of certain members of the New York Army National Guard and the New York Air National Guard to the Standby Reserve as continued by the Executive Order No. 1, dated December 18, 1973
§ 2.9 - Executive order no. 9: establishing the interdepartmental commission on services to children and youth
§ 2.10 - Executive Order No. 10: Relating to extended unemployment insurance benefits
§ 2.11 - Executive order no. 11: relating to equal employment opportunity for women in state government

Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 9, subtit. A, ch. I, pt. 2

Executive Order No. 5 of Governor Eliot Spitzer (9 NYCRR
§ 6.5) repeals, cancels and revokes in their entirety all Executive Orders
issued by previous Governors with the exception of those Executive Orders noted
as being continued in the Text of Executive Order No. 5. State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
